The paper describes the development of a Convolution Neural Network (CNN) for recognizing cane toads in images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques such as CNNs for image recognition is a common application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the training process and optimization of the CNN, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of heat-map Gaussian targets for training the CNN is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE), which is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential application of the CNN in mechanical cane toad traps, which involves robotics and control (cs.RO), making it another possible sub-category.
